              <h5 class="text-theme-colored mt-0 pt-5">Fundraising Strategy Opportunities for Volunteers</h5>
              <p class="mb-20">Do you have experience in helping NGOs with Fundraising? If yes, ODH Foundation is looking for volunteers to work on the following tasks: - Do research on new leads - Help the NGO draft the outreach email and provide suggestions on how best they can engage with donors using new technology. - Help the NGO draft a good proposal. Volunteers can work from any location as it is a remote opportunity. Join and make a difference.</p>
 <p class="mb-20">The ideal candidate for this position is someone who is passionate about our mission, has strong communication and interpersonal skills, and is comfortable working with a diverse group of people.</p>
             
            </div>
              <div id="section-nine" class="mb-50">
                  <h5 class="text-theme-colored mt-0 pt-5">Chartered Accountant Opportunities for Volunteers</h5>
              <p class="mb-20">If you have a Certified Chartered Accountant (CA) with a valid license to practice. Proven experience in financial management, accounting, and taxation. Strong knowledge of accounting principles and standards, as well as tax laws and regulations. Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills. Attention to detail and accuracy in financial reporting and record-keeping. Ability to work collaboratively with other volunteers and staff. Strong communication and interpersonal skills. Commitment to the organization's mission and values. If you are a certified Chartered Accountant and want to use your skills and expertise to make a positive impact, this is an exciting opportunity to get involved with our organization and help us to achieve our financial goals.
                  
</p>
    <h5 class="text-theme-colored mt-0 pt-5">Key Responsibilities:</h5>
              <ul>
                  <li>Manage and maintain accurate financial records for the organization.</li>
                  <br /><li>Review and analyse financial reports and provide recommendations for improving financial performance and efficiency.</li>
                  <br /><li>Develop and implement financial policies and procedures to ensure compliance with legal and regulatory requirements.</li>
                  <br /><li>Assist in budget preparation, monitoring, and reporting. Provide guidance and advice to the organization's staff and volunteers on financial matters. Ensure that all financial transactions are recorded and reported accurately and in a timely manner.</li>
                  <br /><li>Work collaboratively with other volunteers and staff to ensure financial accountability and transparency.</li>
                  <br /><li>Assist in the preparation of financial reports for donors, grant applications, and other external stakeholders.</li>
                  <br /><li>Advise the organization on tax laws and regulations, and ensure that the organization remains in compliance with all relevant tax laws. Participate in audits and other financial reviews as required.</li>
          
              
              </ul>
            </div>
